9998,IssuesEvent,2017-05-31 19:55:44+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,reopened,Absolute path resolve and remove symbolic links,[],[],4,I'm running into an interesting problem with symbolic links in my file paths. I have an R function written in C++ with a parameter being a file path. For example `logfile = ""~/Documents/XXX/YYY""` where `~/Documents` is in fact a symbolic link to another hard drive I have (not mounted to `~/Documents` directly for a reason). Then the C++ program does not leave any logfile behind. If I change the path to the actual link it then works.

